WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.641 --> 00:00:09.633
I'm still waiting. Shawn.

2
00:00:09.977 --> 00:00:13.971
Okay. I'm gonna take your pointy.
sad-faced guy for my horsey guy.

3
00:00:14.047 --> 00:00:16.482
Stop. Stop. What
is this piece called?

4
00:00:16.550 --> 00:00:18.212
I call him Dwight.

5
00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:20.343
What is this one called?

6
00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:21.854
B.A. Baracus.

7
00:00:21.922 --> 00:00:23.299
Look. Shawn. if you're
gonna play this game.

8
00:00:23.323 --> 00:00:25.134
you're gonna have to learn
what the pieces are called.

9
00:00:25.158 --> 00:00:26.922
But what if I don't
wanna play this game?

10
00:00:26.994 --> 00:00:28.929
Chess is important.
It's about strategy.

11
00:00:28.996 --> 00:00:31.431
It's about anticipating your
opponent's next moves.

12
00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:33.330
This game is an
allegory for life.

13
00:00:33.400 --> 00:00:35.130
Alle-what?

14
00:00:35.202 --> 00:00:37.013
Look. when you're on the force.
you're gonna have to take in

15
00:00:37.037 --> 00:00:38.403
huge amounts of information.

16
00:00:38.472 --> 00:00:39.997
Alibis. motives.
witness statements.

17
00:00:40.073 --> 00:00:42.042
And trust me. If you wanna win.

18
00:00:42.276 --> 00:00:44.802
this is not stuff that you're
gonna make up as you go.

19
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:45.878
Do you understand?

20
00:00:45.946 --> 00:00:49.212
Now I want you to
focus and get serious.

21
00:00:52.553 --> 00:00:53.919
SHAWN: Uh.

22
00:00:53.987 --> 00:00:55.785
(STAMMERING) What?
What're you trying to say?

23
00:00:55.856 --> 00:00:57.154
Can't remember what it's called.

24
00:00:57.224 --> 00:00:59.750
What did I just... Oh.
never mind. I remember.

25
00:00:59.826 --> 00:01:01.192
Checkmate.

26
00:01:02.896 --> 00:01:04.159
Bye. Dad.

27
00:01:11.238 --> 00:01:13.571
Tell me. is he cheating on me?

28
00:01:13.640 --> 00:01:14.664
Jury's still out.

29
00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:17.438
Do you have something
that he's touched recently?

30
00:01:17.511 --> 00:01:19.070
Oh.

31
00:01:19.146 --> 00:01:21.377
I have the receipt from lunch.

32
00:01:27.254 --> 00:01:29.814
I'm sensing that he always
takes you out for lunch.

33
00:01:29.957 --> 00:01:31.516
That he never pays
with a credit card.

34
00:01:31.592 --> 00:01:33.220
Always cash. That's right.

35
00:01:33.293 --> 00:01:35.694
I'm also sensing that you
can only call him at the office

36
00:01:35.762 --> 00:01:37.663
or on his cell phone.
never. ever at home.

37
00:01:37.731 --> 00:01:39.529
That's dead on.

38
00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:41.535
You must get goose
bumps being around him.

39
00:01:41.602 --> 00:01:43.833
I get something. Daphne. I
have good news and bad news.

40
00:01:43.904 --> 00:01:46.840
The good news is. he's
not seeing someone else.

41
00:01:46.907 --> 00:01:49.570
The bad news. he's married.

42
00:01:49.643 --> 00:01:53.080
What? Are you sure?

43
00:01:53.146 --> 00:01:55.638
Just tell him a friend
told you he was married.

44
00:01:55.716 --> 00:01:58.242
(SIGHS) and his face
will tell you the rest.

45
00:01:58.619 --> 00:02:01.589
But when the
mourning period is over.

46
00:02:01.655 --> 00:02:03.715
this is my friend Gus's card.

47
00:02:03.790 --> 00:02:06.869
He's a good listener. and he's willing to
change everything about himself for a girl.

48
00:02:06.893 --> 00:02:07.893
Shawn. I do not...

49
00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:09.987
No. no. You keep that. Please.

50
00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:15.868
Shawn. we've reached
a certain level of success.

51
00:02:15.936 --> 00:02:18.963
If you wanna keep doing these "Is
my boyfriend cheating on me?" cases.

52
00:02:19.039 --> 00:02:20.416
you're gonna have
to do them without me.

53
00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:22.409
Gus. you continue
to underestimate me.

54
00:02:22.476 --> 00:02:24.377
I'll have you know that
right now. as we speak.

55
00:02:24.444 --> 00:02:26.589
we're on our way to the office
to meet with two gentlemen

56
00:02:26.613 --> 00:02:29.447
named Shockley and Goddard
who have a very big case for us.

57
00:02:29.516 --> 00:02:31.883
So what are we talking?
Robbery? Missing persons?

58
00:02:31.952 --> 00:02:34.751
They want us to look
into the serious matter of...

59
00:02:35.589 --> 00:02:37.717
Well. that actually
wasn't in the e-mail.

60
00:02:37.791 --> 00:02:38.835
So how do you know it's real?

61
00:02:38.859 --> 00:02:42.159
They used all caps. Gus. The
meeting's at 2:00. We better hurry.

62
00:02:42.229 --> 00:02:43.390
It's 2:18.

63
00:02:43.463 --> 00:02:46.524
Well. somebody had to have the
Belgian chocolate fondue. didn't they?

64
00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:48.091
That was you. Shawn.

65
00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:50.463
Well played. sir.

66
00:02:53.373 --> 00:02:54.671
Just let me do the talking.

67
00:02:54.741 --> 00:02:55.785
I don't want you
to scare them off

68
00:02:55.809 --> 00:02:58.335
with your non
sequitur ridiculousness.

69
00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:03.644
Please tell me you're not
Mr. Shockley and Mr. Goddard.

70
00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:10.356
(SIGHS)

71
00:03:14.261 --> 00:03:17.698
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

72
00:03:17.764 --> 00:03:20.757
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

73
00:03:20.834 --> 00:03:24.032
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

74
00:03:24.104 --> 00:03:28.269
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

75
00:03:34.915 --> 00:03:37.214
Okay. before one of us
goes all crazy and demands

76
00:03:37.284 --> 00:03:40.029
the other one apologize for taking a
case from a couple of grade-schoolers.

77
00:03:40.053 --> 00:03:42.045
let's just hear them out.

78
00:03:44.691 --> 00:03:46.284
What can we do
for you. gentlemen?

79
00:03:46.359 --> 00:03:48.726
One of our teachers
is a murderer.

80
00:03:48.795 --> 00:03:51.424
Okay. I'm sorry.
Please. continue.

81
00:03:51.498 --> 00:03:54.468
He's killed before. and in
two days he's gonna kill again.

82
00:03:54.534 --> 00:03:56.594
And the cops don't listen
to us 'cause we're kids.

83
00:03:56.670 --> 00:03:58.639
Okay. Well. since we're here

84
00:03:58.705 --> 00:04:02.005
and we don't have
another meeting for a week.

85
00:04:02.109 --> 00:04:04.487
which one of your teachers is
going to do this terrible thing?

86
00:04:04.511 --> 00:04:06.241
We don't know.
Who's been murdered?

87
00:04:06.313 --> 00:04:08.111
We don't know.
Who's the next victim?

88
00:04:08.181 --> 00:04:09.410
We don't know. Perfect.

89
00:04:09.483 --> 00:04:11.611
I have no more questions. Shawn?

90
00:04:12.052 --> 00:04:13.543
I got nothing.

91
00:04:13.854 --> 00:04:15.064
Can we just start from the top?

92
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:17.250
Yes. that's a great idea.

93
00:04:17.324 --> 00:04:19.384
Well. Shock and I
go to Meitner and...

94
00:04:19.459 --> 00:04:22.088
The Meitner School
for gifted students?

95
00:04:22.562 --> 00:04:23.825
These kids are geniuses.

96
00:04:23.897 --> 00:04:25.763
Technically. near genius.

97
00:04:26.233 --> 00:04:28.911
The school has some pretty cool
stuff. so we broke in late at night...

98
00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.460
Say no more.

99
00:04:30.537 --> 00:04:31.903
Fight club? No.

100
00:04:32.005 --> 00:04:33.268
To hack into a space probe

101
00:04:33.340 --> 00:04:36.071
and see if we could get it to
blink a word in old Morse code.

102
00:04:36.143 --> 00:04:37.805
Which word?

103
00:04:37.878 --> 00:04:39.278
TOGETHER: (LAUGHING) Boobs.

104
00:04:39.346 --> 00:04:40.690
You went through all
that trouble just to get

105
00:04:40.714 --> 00:04:42.410
some NASA techs
to scratch their heads?

106
00:04:42.516 --> 00:04:43.848
Yeah.

107
00:04:43.917 --> 00:04:45.647
Come on. Gus.
That's kind of funny.

108
00:04:45.719 --> 00:04:47.029
While re-configuring
the receiver.

109
00:04:47.053 --> 00:04:48.817
we accidentally tapped
into a cell phone call

110
00:04:48.889 --> 00:04:50.166
being made from
the Meitner campus.

111
00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:53.957
It was staticky. but we heard a deep.
gravelly voice talking to their cousin.

112
00:04:54.027 --> 00:04:55.120
Someone named Muriel.

113
00:04:55.195 --> 00:04:59.189
And you want us to figure out why
someone would name their kid Muriel?

114
00:04:59.766 --> 00:05:01.098
The voice said something like.

115
00:05:01.168 --> 00:05:03.296
"I'm not gonna be pushed
into a corner again."

116
00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:05.300
Are you sure it
wasn't <i>Dirty Dancing?</i>

117
00:05:05.372 --> 00:05:07.273
And then we also
heard. verbatim.

118
00:05:07.340 --> 00:05:09.673
"If I have to. I'll kill him.

119
00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:13.202
"It won't be my first time.
By Wednesday. he's a goner."

120
00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:16.011
"A goner"? It may have
been James Cagney.

121
00:05:16.082 --> 00:05:18.108
Shawn. can I have a minute?

122
00:05:21.021 --> 00:05:23.752
BOTH: We're taking this case.
You want to take this case?

123
00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:27.317
Miss a chance to go undercover
in high school. a la <i>21 Jump Street?</i>

124
00:05:27.494 --> 00:05:30.931
Obviously. I'm Johnny Depp. Sadly.
you can only pass for Holly Robinson.

125
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:32.197
Why can't I be Richard Grieco?

126
00:05:32.265 --> 00:05:34.257
Why would you wanna
be Richard Grieco?

127
00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:37.361
Isn't this the part where you say.
"There ain't no case here. Shawn.

128
00:05:37.437 --> 00:05:40.236
"Just a couple of
kids crying wolf."

129
00:05:40.307 --> 00:05:43.072
I don't sound like Richard
Roundtree. Shawn.

130
00:05:43.143 --> 00:05:44.338
Why are you so eager?

131
00:05:44.444 --> 00:05:46.436
Same as you. I was
a king in high school.

132
00:05:46.513 --> 00:05:48.524
Just because you carried a
scepter. doesn't make you a king.

133
00:05:48.548 --> 00:05:49.759
That was because
I was in <i>Macbeth.</i>

134
00:05:49.783 --> 00:05:51.376
Dude. you played Banquo's kid.

135
00:05:51.451 --> 00:05:53.682
Hey. guys. Can you help us?

136
00:05:54.421 --> 00:05:56.890
Is a lizard's skin
dry and cracked?

137
00:05:57.924 --> 00:05:59.119
(WHISPERING)

138
00:06:02.629 --> 00:06:03.961
We believe that it is.

139
00:06:14.507 --> 00:06:15.507
Guess what today is?

140
00:06:15.575 --> 00:06:17.486
(SCOFFS) It's not one of
those touchy. feely holidays

141
00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:18.788
invented by card
companies to goad me

142
00:06:18.812 --> 00:06:21.023
into buying a present for someone
I couldn't care less about. is it?

143
00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:22.413
No. Today's our anniversary.

144
00:06:22.482 --> 00:06:24.110
Come again?

145
00:06:24.184 --> 00:06:27.985
It's been one year to the day that I came
to Santa Barbara and we got partnered up.

146
00:06:28.054 --> 00:06:29.920
Oh. I didn't get you a present.

147
00:06:29.990 --> 00:06:31.253
I don't want a present. Yeah.

148
00:06:31.324 --> 00:06:34.658
That's what all women say. But believe
me. deep down you'll want a present.

149
00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:36.959
My soon-to-be ex-wife
always hated what I gave her.

150
00:06:37.030 --> 00:06:39.090
Well. what did you
give her? Cash. mostly.

151
00:06:39.165 --> 00:06:41.327
Ugh. Anyway.

152
00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:44.235
This anniversary means that my
one-year probation period is over.

153
00:06:44.304 --> 00:06:46.796
So. what I want.

154
00:06:46.873 --> 00:06:49.638
that is. what would be good...
What I'm trying to say is.

155
00:06:49.709 --> 00:06:52.645
I think I'm entitled to
be primary on a case.

156
00:06:54.314 --> 00:06:55.942
How late are the
shops open tonight?

157
00:06:56.016 --> 00:06:58.451
Chief Vick says molding
young officers is your duty.

158
00:06:58.518 --> 00:07:00.749
and she's already approved this.

159
00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:02.311
Now give me a case.

160
00:07:02.522 --> 00:07:03.546
(SIGHS)

161
00:07:03.623 --> 00:07:04.716
Fine.

162
00:07:07.827 --> 00:07:11.923
See. Homicide. That's a
bit messy for your first time.

163
00:07:11.998 --> 00:07:15.491
Hi-tech burglary. You need
a lot of forensics for that one.

164
00:07:15.568 --> 00:07:17.059
Bake sale slap fight.

165
00:07:17.137 --> 00:07:19.663
Seems easy. but believe
me. I worked one once.

166
00:07:19.739 --> 00:07:22.709
I had to call in
SWAT. Oh. come on.

167
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.369
All right.

168
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:27.744
A couple of kids came in
complaining about one of their teachers.

169
00:07:27.814 --> 00:07:30.784
Are you sure there's nothing of
lower priority for me to handle?

170
00:07:30.850 --> 00:07:36.289
Lesson number one. O'Hara. There
are no small cases. only small detectives.

171
00:07:38.158 --> 00:07:39.524
Let's roll.

172
00:07:43.797 --> 00:07:45.425
SHAWN: Ah. high school.

173
00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:48.511
You know. I've always wanted to prove
that one of our teachers was a monster.

174
00:07:48.535 --> 00:07:50.713
You remember our freshman
music teacher. Mrs. Jorgenstorm?

175
00:07:50.737 --> 00:07:52.103
She was a Nightbreed.
She was not.

176
00:07:52.172 --> 00:07:53.749
She used to date Craig
Schiffer. She did not.

177
00:07:53.773 --> 00:07:56.607
She wore a ton of make-up and
lived in a cemetery. Next to a cemetery.

178
00:07:56.676 --> 00:07:58.474
So she claimed. If I
remember correctly.

179
00:07:58.545 --> 00:08:01.140
you were always too
afraid to follow her home.

180
00:08:01.214 --> 00:08:02.214
So. any leads yet?

181
00:08:02.282 --> 00:08:04.308
Hold it there. Doogie.
First things first.

182
00:08:04.417 --> 00:08:06.909
Where do I get a juice box and
does it come in grape-a-licious?

183
00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:08.819
Shouldn't you be
doing psychic stuff?

184
00:08:08.888 --> 00:08:12.052
I mean. someone could be killed in
the next 48 hours. Possibly one of us.

185
00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:15.118
(CHUCKLES) If you're so smart.
why don't you solve the thing?

186
00:08:15.195 --> 00:08:17.164
Midterms? Duh!

187
00:08:17.230 --> 00:08:19.961
I need to maintain my GPA to
keep my scholarship stipend.

188
00:08:20.033 --> 00:08:21.077
All right. All right. All right.

189
00:08:21.101 --> 00:08:23.379
Clearly. we have to get inside.
What's our cover gonna be?

190
00:08:23.403 --> 00:08:24.962
Wait. I've got it.

191
00:08:25.038 --> 00:08:27.183
You're the preppy jerk who's
dating the girl I'm in love with.

192
00:08:27.207 --> 00:08:29.652
I'm the lonely cafeteria guy who
mows lawns and has a heart of gold.

193
00:08:29.676 --> 00:08:31.577
Let it go. Shawn. You
can't pass for a teenager.

194
00:08:31.644 --> 00:08:34.443
Yeah. he's right. You got
rhytids around the eyes.

195
00:08:34.514 --> 00:08:36.312
What did he just say
to me? The crow's feet.

196
00:08:36.383 --> 00:08:39.114
Do you squint or
make funny faces a lot?

197
00:08:39.753 --> 00:08:41.278
You know what?
You guys are all nuts.

198
00:08:41.388 --> 00:08:44.051
If I grew my hair out. raised
my voice an octave. I could...

199
00:08:44.124 --> 00:08:45.752
Stop. Shawn. I've
already worked it out.

200
00:08:45.825 --> 00:08:50.320
We're documentarians working on a
new film called <i>Teeniuses: In the Mix.</i>

201
00:08:50.397 --> 00:08:51.990
"Teeniuses"? Yes.

202
00:08:52.065 --> 00:08:55.866
Really. dude? You got "Teeniuses"
right on the tip of your tongue?

203
00:08:55.935 --> 00:08:58.871
<i>In the Mix.</i> We already
got your cover story.

204
00:08:59.506 --> 00:09:04.501
Personally. I'm not sure that I see the
merits of a class in paranormal studies.

205
00:09:04.577 --> 00:09:08.844
but we do let the students choose
one guest instructor a semester.

206
00:09:08.915 --> 00:09:11.976
C. Everett Koop was
crushed that he didn't get it.

207
00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:16.021
What is this. like a study hall?

208
00:09:16.089 --> 00:09:17.648
Oh. no. Recess.

209
00:09:20.493 --> 00:09:21.517
(SNIFFS)

210
00:09:21.594 --> 00:09:23.859
Does it smell like
teen spirit in here?

211
00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:25.364
(SHUSHING)

212
00:09:35.075 --> 00:09:39.706
So. tell me. Headmaster. Can a
former applicant request his or her file?

213
00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:41.714
Oh. no. Why?

214
00:09:41.781 --> 00:09:44.148
Oh. for the general
public's general welfare.

215
00:09:44.217 --> 00:09:45.776
You know. generally.

216
00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:50.718
Debby will give you the
forms you'll need to sign.

217
00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:54.721
An application. Gus?

218
00:09:54.794 --> 00:09:55.955
Just curious.

219
00:09:56.029 --> 00:09:58.225
You applied to this school
back in the day. didn't you?

220
00:09:58.298 --> 00:09:59.475
And you didn't tell me about it.

221
00:09:59.499 --> 00:10:00.609
Who could remember
that far back?

222
00:10:00.633 --> 00:10:01.896
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

223
00:10:01.968 --> 00:10:04.028
Is that why you cried for a
month when we were 10?

224
00:10:04.104 --> 00:10:06.596
Because they rejected
you? Get down!

225
00:10:13.046 --> 00:10:14.674
Excuse me. O'Hara?

226
00:10:16.483 --> 00:10:19.817
Lesson number two. Cops don't wait
in line. They go straight to the front.

227
00:10:19.886 --> 00:10:21.320
Even at Starbucks.

228
00:10:21.387 --> 00:10:22.616
Hi. SBPD.

229
00:10:22.689 --> 00:10:25.329
Can I please get the class schedules
for these students? Thank you.

230
00:10:25.391 --> 00:10:27.155
Lesson number three.
Don't say "Please."

231
00:10:27.227 --> 00:10:29.662
don't say "Thank you."
and definitely don't say "Hi."

232
00:10:29.729 --> 00:10:31.823
Spirit squad auditions
were over 10 years ago.

233
00:10:31.898 --> 00:10:34.060
You're an authority
figure. Act like it.

234
00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:35.744
Ever heard. "You catch
more flies with honey"?

235
00:10:35.768 --> 00:10:38.499
Lesson number four. Don't quote
cornpone country bumpkin sayings

236
00:10:38.571 --> 00:10:39.869
to your commanding officer.

237
00:10:39.939 --> 00:10:41.237
How many lessons are there?

238
00:10:41.307 --> 00:10:43.037
Six hundred thirty-eight.

239
00:10:43.109 --> 00:10:45.521
Welcome to the Meitner School
